 <td valign="top" class="vt-content">
 

	
  <div class="vt-datebar">
  <img src="./styles/absolution/imageset/icon_post_target.gif" width="11" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" />Posted: Thu Jul 01, 2010 7:47 pm 
  </div><!-- /vt-datebar --> 
            
       <div class="vt-postcontent">
       I've got RAID0 up and running on my Stora with (2) HDDs.
<br />
<br />I'll just give an overview, if you want details let me know.
<br />
<br />1. Activated stock Stora w/ (2) Terabyte drives synced w/RAID1 (I should have activated without any drives inserted)
<br />2. I ran the "StoraUnlock.exe" that I found in the forums here on this site.
<br />3. SSH into Stora
<br />4. I ran "chkconfig --level 12345 /etc/init.d/netgear-lifecyle off
<br />5. I ran "shutdown -r now"
<br />6. I ran "df -k" and umounted anything mounted on /dev/md0 (i.e. umount /tmp)
<br />9. I ran "mdadm --manage --fail /dev/md0 /dev/sda"
<br />10. I ran "mdadm --manage --fail /dev/md0 /dev/sdb"
<br />11. I ran "mdadm --manage --remove /dev/md0 /dev/sda"
<br />12. I ran "mdadm --manage --remove /dev/md0 /dev/sdb"
<br />13. I ran "mdadm --stop /dev/md0
<br />14 I edited "vi /usr/lib/spd/scripts/raid/RaidArrayClass.php" about halfway through file change value "level=1" to "level=0"
<br />15. I ran "shutdown -r now" and after reboot the Stora rebuilt the array with RAID0!!!
<br />
<br />I apologize for the sloppy sloppy instructions...I pretty much just hacked around and googled until I got the unit to stop saying device busy when ever I tried to remove the drive from the array...
       </div> 
       
       

    
    
 </td><!-- /content -->
